Subject: [RFC/RFT v2 option 0/4] clk: sunxi-ng: keep Cubie A7S SDMMC0 path live

This is a local v2 option for the A733 CCU/NSI series. It keeps the
same hardware-proven A733 critical-clock set as the submitted RFC/RFT,
but expresses the NSI update-bit fix in common sunxi-ng registration
code instead of as an A733-specific probe-time write.

The common update-bit patch is intentionally broader than the submitted
A733-specific form: it commits boot-programmed state once for every
clock carrying CCU_FEATURE_UPDATE_BIT in a registered CCU descriptor.
That may be preferable if maintainers want the feature flag to own this
semantic, but it should not replace the narrow A733 form unless reviewers
ask for common handling.

Validation performed on this local option:

- git am --3way from the recorded base
- git diff --check
- scripts/checkpatch.pl --strict --show-types
- focused arm64 GCC W=1 object builds for ccu_common.o,
  ccu-sun55i-a523.o, and ccu-sun60i-a733.o
- focused sparse C=1 checks for the same objects

Enzo Adriano (4):
  clk: sunxi-ng: a733: keep the CPUS AHB bridge clock critical
  clk: sunxi-ng: a733: keep storage and NSI fabric clocks critical
  clk: sunxi-ng: commit update-bit clocks during registration
  clk: sunxi-ng: a733: keep GIC and CPU peri clocks critical

